# Sūra XCVII.: Qadr, or The Night of Power (or Honour).

### Section 1

![](../gif/097/097_001.gif)

1. Inn<u>a</u> anzaln<u>a</u>hu fee laylati alqadr**i**

1\. We have indeed revealed  
This (Message)  
In the Night of Power:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/097/097_002.gif)

2. Wam<u>a</u> adr<u>a</u>ka m<u>a</u> laylatu alqadr**i**

2\. And what will explain  
To thee what the Night  
Of Power is?

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/097/097_003.gif)

3. Laylatu alqadri khayrun min alfi shahr**in**

3\. The Night of Power  
Is better than  
A thousand Months,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/097/097_004.gif)

4. Tanazzalu almal<u>a</u>-ikatu wa**al**rroo<u>h</u>u feeh<u>a</u>
bi-i<u>th</u>ni rabbihim min kulli amr**in**

4\. Therein come dawn  
The angels and the Spirit  
By God's permission,  
On every errand:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/097/097_005.gif)

5. Sal<u>a</u>mun hiya <u>h</u>att<u>a</u> ma<u>t</u>laAAi alfajr**i**

5\. Peace!…This  
Until the rise of Morn!

